"Abstract The security of the asymmetric cryptosystem MST 1 {{}_{1}} relies on the hardness of factoring group elements with respect to a logarithmic signature. In this paper we investigate the factorization problem with respect to logarithmic signatures of abelian groups represented in primary decomposition. We present an efficient factorization algorithm for logarithmic signatures, where descending into factor groups induced by period subgroups is possible. Especially, we show that a logarithmic signature is tame when all its blocks are of prime size."
